SIMPLE: scaphoid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scaphoid
<hw>Scaph"oid</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ska`fh</grk> a boat + <ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>scapho⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Resembling a
boat in form; boat-shaped.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The
scaphoid bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scaphoid bone</b></col> <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>One of the
carpal bones, which articulates with the radius; the radiale</cd>.
<sd>(b)</sd> <cd>One of the tarsal bones; the navicular bone. See under
<er>Navicular</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapholunar</ent>⟦br⟧
